race.comment: NORWOODS (4) is knocking on the door, running a strong race here last time out over this route, working home well for second. He should land in a positive spot here from the inside gate and will take plenty of catching down in grade. SHOWMARA (2) has been solid in two runs back, boxing on well for a narrow fourth when in the market at Kilmore second up. He should be ready to peak now up to a suitable trip and with any luck early he can run well. CHA CHA CHANGES (8) resumes. This is a good trip for her first up off a trial win and compared to the rest of the field she's relatively lightly raced. WILLIAMSTOWN (1) was close up at Echuca last time out when third in a highweight race and he has each-way claims again. ATAEGINA (5) is drawn to get back but can be hitting the line.
